President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the reappointment of Mrs. Folashade Joseph as the Managing Director/CEO of Nigerian Agricultural Insurance Corporation (NAIC) for a second term. This is contained in a letter signed by the Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Sabo Nanono. The letter stated that the reappointment will take effect from April 11, 2021. It added that her reappointment was based on her hard work, dedication, commitment, service delivery as well as her contribution towards the progress and upliftment of NAIC. The Minister urged her to use her reappointment to bring to bear her wealth of experience in driving the activities of the corporation in accordance with its mandate, enabling act and subsisting laws.